<concept id="concept_3413BBD173324104B42FB714974CABE7" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Addressing the Platform Services - REST</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>In order to address resources of <ph conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> by means of the REST API, you use URLs built according to the following format: </p>
            <p><codeph>https://&lt;host>:&lt;port>/&lt;basePath>/&lt;resource></codeph></p>
            <p><codeph>&lt;host></codeph> and <codeph>&lt;port></codeph> point to the server where <ph
                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> has been deployed. <codeph>&lt;basePath></codeph> is the <codeph>basePath</codeph> stated in the YAML file; it consists of the relevant <ph
                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> component and the API version. <codeph>&lt;resource></codeph> is the resource path.</p>
            <p>Example:</p>
            <p><codeph>https://myserver:8081/oscm-trigger/v1/triggers</codeph></p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>